INT. CABIN - NIGHT

The fire crackles. Snow piles against the windows.

WREN
We should have turned back at the ridge.

===

INT. CABIN - LATER

The fire has burned down to embers. Wren is asleep in a chair.

A knock at the door. Three slow knocks.

===

INT. CABIN - CONTINUOUS

Wren startles awake. The knocking comes again, closer this time.

WREN
(whispering)
Who's there?

No answer. Just the wind.
